{
  "texts": [
    "We also utilized open-sourced models, Falcon-40B [50] and Llama-2-70b [51] which are amongst the most powerful open-sourced models.",
    "These specific models were chosen because they are the largest LLMs with some of the best published performance characteristics.",
    "We felt they were the only ones likely to have comparable performance to GPT-4, which is widely considered the gold standard for LLMs.",
    "In general, we expect models to perform better as the number of parameters increases, but the specifics of the training data may have a nontrivial impact on model performance as well.",
    "For example, some LLMs may have been trained on more coding text, allowing them to perform better in these cases."
  ]
}